% You are an expert TypeScript React engineer. Generate `pdd/frontend/components/JobCard.tsx` as the job summary/action card used by the jobs dashboard.

% Requirements
1) Export a default `JobCard` React functional component using this prop contract:
   - `job: JobInfo`
   - `isSelected: boolean`
   - `onSelect: () => void`
   - `onCancel: () => void`
   - `onRemove?: () => void`
   - `onMarkDone?: (success: boolean) => void`
   - `onMarkStatus?: (status: 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled') => void`
2) Import `React` and import `JobInfo` + `JobStatus` from `../hooks/useJobs`.
3) Keep helper `formatDuration(startedAt, completedAt)`:
   - Use `completedAt || new Date()` as end time.
   - Return `Xs` for under a minute, `Xm Ys` for under an hour, and `Xh Ym` otherwise.
4) Keep helper `formatTimeAgo(date)`:
   - Return `Xs ago`, `Xm ago`, `Xh ago`, or `Xd ago` based on elapsed time.
5) Keep helper `extractDevUnitName(displayCommand)`:
   - Prefer prompt path match `prompts/<name>...` and return `<name>`.
   - Fallback to `<module>_<Language>.prompt` and return `<module>`.
   - Fallback to CLI module flags `-m <module>` or `--module <module>`.
   - Return `null` if no pattern matches.
6) Keep helper `getStatusStyle(status: JobStatus)` returning `{ bg, text, icon }` with:
   - `queued -> clock` (yellow classes)
   - `running -> spinner` (accent classes)
   - `completed -> check` (green classes)
   - `failed -> x` (red classes)
   - `cancelled -> slash` (surface classes)
   - fallback `question` (surface classes)
7) Derive component state from `job`:
   - `isActive` when status is `queued` or `running`
   - `isSpawnedJob` when `job.id` starts with `spawned-`
   - `isRemoteJob` when `job.metadata?.remote === true`
   - `devUnitName = extractDevUnitName(job.displayCommand)`
   - `progressPercent = Math.round((current / total) * 100)` when `job.progress` exists, else `null`
8) Make the card root clickable (`onClick={onSelect}`), with selected vs non-selected Tailwind styling (border/background/shadow transition).
9) Header content:
   - Show truncated `job.displayCommand` as title with full command in `title`.
   - Show a small dev-unit badge when `devUnitName` exists.
   - Show status pill with text `job.status` and inline SVG icon chosen by `statusStyle.icon`.
   - Show timing text:
     - active jobs: running duration from `formatDuration(job.startedAt, null)`
     - completed jobs with `completedAt`: `formatTimeAgo(job.completedAt)`
     - otherwise fallback to duration from start
10) Show cost only when `job.cost > 0`, formatted as dollars with 3 decimals.
11) Show determinate progress bar only when `isActive && progressPercent !== null`:
   - Left label is `job.progress?.message || 'Processing...'`
   - Right label is `${progressPercent}%`
   - Bar width uses inline style `${progressPercent}%`
12) Show indeterminate bar only when `job.status === 'running' && progressPercent === null` using `animate-indeterminate`.
13) Show output preview only when `job.output.length > 0`, rendering the last output line in a monospace truncated line.
14) Action buttons must stop propagation so clicking them does not trigger card selection.
15) For active spawned local jobs (`isActive && isSpawnedJob && !isRemoteJob && onMarkDone`):
   - Show `Done` button calling `onMarkDone(true)`
   - Show `Failed` button calling `onMarkDone(false)`
   - If `onRemove` exists, show `Dismiss` button calling `onRemove`
16) For active remote jobs when `onMarkStatus` exists:
   - Show `Done` (`completed`), `Failed` (`failed`), and `Cancelled` (`cancelled`) buttons calling `onMarkStatus(...)`
17) For active remote jobs (regardless of `onMarkStatus`), show a disabled-looking `Cancel Remote (Coming Soon)` button that triggers an alert explaining it is not fully implemented yet and manual status buttons should be used.
18) For active regular async jobs (`isActive && !isSpawnedJob && !isRemoteJob`), show `Cancel` button calling `onCancel`.
19) For non-active jobs, show `Remove` only when `onRemove` exists.
20) Always render the trailing action button that calls `onSelect` and shows:
   - `Details` for spawned jobs
   - `View Output` otherwise

% Constraints
- Keep dark-theme Tailwind utility styling consistent with the rest of the dashboard UI.
- Keep all icons as inline SVG.
- Keep the component self-contained in one file and default-export `JobCard`.

% Deliverable
- Output only `pdd/frontend/components/JobCard.tsx`.
